    "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\n- `vim.paste()` (`nvim_paste`) and clipboard put (`\"+p`) doesn't understand image contents or URLs (e.g. in a markdown file).\r\n- Overriding the [clipboard provider](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/0ca2d11c1f473d9924c261c9dbd4e38730932bb4/runtime/autoload/provider/clipboard.vim#L1) is awkward. It should just be a function, similar to `vim.paste`.\r\n\r\n# Expected behavior\r\n\r\n- Convert all providers to `vim.ui.*` functions, e.g. clipboard provider is exposed as `vim.ui.clipboard()`\r\n    - #27119\r\n- Support buffer-local (filetype) handlers for `vim.paste` (and clipboard?).\r\n    - Related: ([on_func()](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/22598))\r\n- Detect binary content and pass a flag to `vim.paste` ?\r\n- Markdown filetype: default handling of image/URL paste\r\n    - When a URL is pasted over a visual selection, replace the selected `text` with `[text](<url>)`.\r\n    - When an image is pasted, do something like [clipboard-image.nvim](https://github.com/ekickx/clipboard-image.nvim/blob/d1550dc26729b7954f95269952e90471b838fa25/lua/clipboard-image/utils.lua#L18-L42): \r\n        1. save the image to CWD\r\n        2. create a `<image src=\"...\">` reference to it.\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\n- https://github.com/sindresorhus/file-type looks useful: \"detect filetype by checking the [magic number](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magic_number_(programming)#Magic_numbers_in_files) of a buffer.\"\r\n- https://github.com/HakonHarnes/img-clip.nvim",
